{"type":"message","id":"8211977e","parentId":"7b0781bc","timestamp":"2026-04-25T22:06:56.460Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The route-camera.html is in the root of agent-mission-control, not in the dist folder. The HTTPS server only serves files from `dist/` directory. So route-camera.html isn't being served by that server.\n\nLet me check if there's a way to serve the route-camera.html or if we need to start a different server for it. I could also add it to the dist directory, or update the HTTPS server to serve it.\n\nLet me think about the simplest fix. The route-camera.html is at ~/agent-mission-control/route-camera.html. For Bobby to access it on his phone, it needs to be served over HTTPS on port 3443.\n\nThe simplest solution is to either:\n1. Copy route-camera.html to the dist folder\n2. Update the HTTPS server to also serve files from the root directory\n\n\n3. Or just start a separate HTTP server for the route camera on a different port and rely on the existing HTTPS setup.\n\nActually, I think adding a route-camera server to serve-apps.cjs makes the most sense. I need to check what's already running on port 8787 since the static-server.cjs is using it, and figure out which ports are actually available to use.\n","thinkingSignature":"2612833952f56a975663a7e9f70f8966a132f1f4fefa1aaa229ff9f8b25f56e2"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qvp3dq2y5nx6_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ps aux | grep -E \"node.*8787|static-server\\|mission-control-api\" | grep -v grep"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_qvp3dq2y5nx6_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"curl -s http://localhost:8787/ 2>&1 | head -10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":78,"output":327,"cacheRead":38912,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":39317,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777154812222,"responseId":"063c6d