{"type":"message","id":"899fe080","parentId":"3edca13f","timestamp":"2026-04-25T22:16:19.771Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_0ak4kszn8k7q_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"const https = require('https');\nconst http = require('http');\nconst fs = require('fs');\nconst path = require('path');\n\n// HTTPS server with static files + /tools proxy\nconst options = {\n  key: fs.readFileSync('/tmp/key.pem'),\n  cert: fs.readFileSync('/tmp/cert.pem'),\n};\n\nconst distDir = path.join(\"/Users/bobbygalletta/agent-mission-control\", 'dist');\n\nconst server = https.createServer(options, (req, res) => {\n  const url = req.url.split('?')[0];\n\n  // Proxy /tools to gateway\n  if (url.startsWith('/tools')) {\n    const proxyReq = http.request({\n      hostname: '127.0.0.1',\n      port: 18789,\n      path: url,\n      method: req.method,\n      headers: req.headers,\n    }, (proxyRes) => {\n      res.writeHead(proxyRes.statusCode, proxyRes.headers);\n      proxyRes.pipe(res);\n    });\n    req.pipe(proxyReq);\n    return;\n  }\n\n  // Serve static files from dist\n  let filePath = path.join(distDir, url === '/' ? 'index.html' : url);\n  if (!fs.existsSync(filePath) || fs.statSync(filePath).isDirectory()) {\n    filePath = path.join(distDir, 'index.html');\n  }\n  const ext = path.extname(filePath);\n  const mimeTypes = {\n    '.html': 'text/html', '.js': 'application/javascript',\n    '.css': 'text/css', '.json': 'application/json',\n    '.png': 'image/png', '.jpg': 'image/jpeg', '.svg': 'image/svg+xml',\n  };\n  res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': mimeTypes[ext] || 'text/plain' });\n  fs.createReadStream(filePath).pipe(res);\n});\n\nserver.listen(3443, '0.0.0.0', () => {\n  console.log('HTTPS Agent Chat: https://100.103.22.35:3443/#/agent-chat');\n});"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1777155379771}}
{"type":"message","id":"3757230a","parentId":"899fe080","timestamp":"2026-04-25T22:16:22.625Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The server-https.cjs serves from the `dist` directory. When someone goes to `/`, it serves `dist/index.html` which is Mission Control. I need to modify the server to serve route-camera.html as the default for `/`, or better yet, just update the server to make route-camera the default or serve it at a specific path that Bobby expects.\n\nActually, the simplest fix is to make the root (`/`) serve route-camera.html instead of index.html. But wait - Bobby was going to `https://100.103.22.35:3443/` and getting Mission Control. Maybe the old behavior was that it DID serve route-camera at `/`. \n\nI think the best approach is to check if there's a route-camera.html in the dist folder and serve it at the root instead of the current index.html. That way Bobby gets what he expects when he visits the base URL.\n","thinkingSignature":"f22776673f15de38b47d611ca5ba7e1a1171ecdceed5ca130ad20a281649934c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_vg771rqo7weh_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/agent-mission-control/dist/route-camera.html && echo \"exists\""}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":594,"output":221,"cacheRead":41408,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":42223,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1777155379773,"responseId":"063c70338dd2def8ebdd72dd2ba9390a"}}
